Introduction

https://health-infobase.canada.ca/covid-19/dashboard/about.html

# devtools::install_github("derekmichaelwright/agData")
library(agData) # Loads: tidyverse, ggpubr, ggbeeswarm, ggrepel
# Prep data
areas <- c("Canada", "Quebec", "Ontario", "British Columbia", 
           "Alberta", "Saskatchewan", "Manitoba", "Nova Scotia",
           "Newfoundland and Labrador", "New Brunswick", "Prince Edward Island", 
           "Northwest Territories", "Yukon", "Nunavut", "Repatriated travellers")
dd <- read.csv("https://health-infobase.canada.ca/src/data/covidLive/covid19-download.csv") %>%
  rename(area=prname) %>%
  mutate(area = factor(area, levels = areas),
         date = as.Date(date, format = "%Y-%m-%d"),
         numdeathstoday = ifelse(numdeathstoday < 0, 0, numdeathstoday),
         numtoday = ifelse(numtoday < 0, 0, numtoday))
DT::datatable(dd)
xx <- dd %>% filter(date == max(date)) %>% 
  select(area, numdeaths) %>% 
  arrange(desc(numdeaths))
DT::datatable(xx)

Cases

# Plot
mp <- ggplot(dd, aes(x = date, y = numtoday, color = area)) + 
  geom_line() + 
  facet_wrap(area ~ ., ncol = 5) +
  theme_agData(legend.position = "none") +
  labs(title = "Daily COVID-19 Cases in Canada", y = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Government of Canada")
ggsave("Canada_COVID_01.png", mp, width = 10, height = 6)

# Plot
mp <- mp + facet_wrap(area ~ ., ncol = 5, scales = "free_y") 
ggsave("Canada_COVID_02.png", mp, width = 10, height = 6)

Canada

# Create Plotting Function
gg_COVID <- function(x, Area) {
  x <- x %>% 
    filter(area == Area) %>% 
    select(area, date, Cases=numtoday, Deaths=numdeathstoday, 
           Cases_cum=numtotal, Deaths_cum=numdeaths) %>%
    gather(Trait, Value, Cases, Deaths, Cases_cum, Deaths_cum) %>%
    mutate(Element = plyr::mapvalues(Trait, c("Cases","Deaths","Cases_cum","Deaths_cum"),
                                     c("Daily", "Daily", "Cummulative", "Cummulative")),
           Trait = plyr::mapvalues(Trait, c("Cases_cum", "Deaths_cum"), c("Cases", "Deaths")))
  # Plot
  ggplot(x, aes(x = date, y = Value, color = Trait)) + 
    geom_line(size = 1) + 
    scale_color_manual(name = NULL, values = c("darkgreen","darkred")) +
    facet_wrap(Element ~ ., scales = "free_y") +
    scale_x_date(date_breaks = "1 month", date_labels = "%b") +
    theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
    labs(title = paste(Area, "COVID-19 Data"), y = NULL, x = NULL,
         caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Government of Canada")
}
# Plot
mp <- gg_COVID(x = dd, Area = "Canada")
ggsave("Canada_COVID_05.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)

Death Rate

lastdate <- max(as.Date(dd$date))
pp <- agData_STATCAN_Population %>% filter(Year == 2019) %>%
  select(area=Area, population=Value)
xx <- dd %>% filter(date == lastdate) %>%
  select(area, numtotal, numdeaths, numtested) %>%
  left_join(pp, by = "area") %>%
  mutate(DeathPerCase = 100 * numdeaths / numtotal,
         DeathPerPop  = 100 * numdeaths / population,
         CasesPerPop  = 100 * numtotal / population) %>%
  filter(!is.na(area)) %>%
  gather(Trait, Value, DeathPerCase, DeathPerPop, CasesPerPop) %>%
  mutate(Trait = plyr::mapvalues(Trait, c("DeathPerCase", "DeathPerPop", "CasesPerPop"),
                   c("Deaths / Cases", "Deaths / Population", "Cases / Population")))
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = area, y = Value, fill = Trait)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", color = "black") +
  facet_grid(Trait ~ ., scales = "free_y") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("darkblue","darkgreen","darkred")) +
  theme_agData(legend.position = "none", rotx = T) +
  labs(title = "COVID-19 Death and Infection Rates", y = "Percentage (%)", x = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Government of Canada")
ggsave("Canada_COVID_10.png", mp, width = 6, height = 8)

Pandemic 1918

library(readxl)
xx <- read_xls("pnas_0610941104_10941Table11.xls", range = "A2:AM27", col_names = F)[-2,] %>%
  t() %>% as.data.frame()
colnames(xx) <- xx[1,]
xx<- xx %>% slice(-1) %>%
  mutate(City = as.Date(as.numeric(City), origin = "1899-12-30")) %>%
  gather(Area, Value, 2:ncol(.)) %>%
  mutate(Value = as.numeric(Value)) %>%
  rename(Date = City)
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = Date, y = Value, color = Area)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(Area ~ ., nrow = 3) +
  theme_agData(legend.position = "none") +
  labs(title = "1918 Pandemic Death Rate / 100,000", y = NULL, x = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Collins et al. 1930")
ggsave("Canada_COVID_11.png", mp, width = 10, height = 4)

xx <- xx %>% filter(Date < "1919-01-11")
xx %>% 
  group_by(Area) %>% 
  summarise(Sum = sum(Value, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  arrange(Sum)
